<HEADLINE>
CLIPPERS AND LAKERS PLAY _ SUMMER LEAGUE STYLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SEAN KEARNS  
 c.2000 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONG BEACH _ So Shaq wasn't there. Neither was Kobe. For that
matter neither were Clippers first-round picks Darius Miles, Keyon
Dooling nor Quentin Richardson.
</P>
<P>
   More than half the players representing the two franchises won't
even be in the NBA at the start of next season. Nonetheless, the
Lakers and Clippers waged the battle of L.A. at the Pyramid on
Monday _ Summer Pro League style.
</P>
<P>
   The Clippers won 88-84.
</P>
<P>
   While Cory Hightower continued to show a solid offensive game,
it was two players _ Laker Devean George and Clipper Brian Skinner,
entering their second seasons _ who impressed a half-full Pyramid.
</P>
<P>
   George scored 27 points and had the Clippers scrambling to make
sure he was covered on the perimeter.
</P>
<P>
   ``Devean is playing real well for two games into the summer
league,'' Lakers summer league coach Jim Cleamons said. ``I qualify
that by saying anyone can play well for two games in summer league.
What we are hoping to do in summer league is see if a player can
sustain his effort over the course of the week of 10 days that
we're there. He's showing the maturity and development we would
like to see.''
</P>
<P>
   Clippers summer league coach Dennis Johnson said he can see the
difference in George over the course of a year. Johnson, while
coaching with the LaCrosse Bobcats in the CBA, scouted George, who
played at Augsburg College in Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's much better now than last year when he came in,'' Johnson
said. ``He's more mature.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Skinner showed no effects from his left-ankle sprain
that left him sidelined for 43 games last season. He scored 21
points and finished with nine rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   He thoroughly test-drove the ankle, diving for loose balls,
getting knocked down and playing 42 minutes. He said the ankle felt
good.
</P>
<P>
   ``For my first game in five months, I thought I did fairly
well,'' Skinner said.
</P>
<P>
   No current first-round draft picks played in the game. Lakers
rookie Mark Madsen continued to sit out with an injured forearm.
</P>
<P>
   The Clippers rookies are not playing because their agents didn't
think it would be a good idea until the Clippers get a coach.
</P>
<P>
   The only drafted rookie who played was Hightower, who finished
with 12 points on 6-of-13 shooting.
</P>
<P>
   The game was the debut of Johnson as assistant coach/summer
league coach. Johnson, a candidate for the head coaching job, said
he was focusing on coaching the team.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was trying to get our team to win,'' Johnson said. ``When
you are out there you are not trying to show anybody anything. I
guaranteed my team if we do this and do that, then we'll be OK.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
