</P>
<P>
   EPISCOPALIANS _ Episcopalians, meeting this week in Denver, are
expected to once again tackle the issue of the rights of Gays
within the denomination. Church members are also expected to debate
and vote on a number of other issues that may have more resonance
on the local level than the sometimes fuzzy issue of homosexuality.
Delegates plan to break into small groups to discuss racism,
violence, ethnic diversity, liturgy and end-of-life issues. The
meeting ends on Thursday. (GWhite, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20.
</P>
