<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ If you think Atlanta's gasoline prices
are high, just take a trip to the Midwest. While traveling through
Missouri, Iowa, Minnesota, Wisconsin and Illinois in the past two
weeks, I have paid as much as $1.90 for regular and talked to
drivers who have paid as much as $2.15 per gallon. (Sharp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
