   THE-MECHANIC _ (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   PTCRUISER _ The Cruiser is hot. Not as in hot rod, which it
looks like, nor as in stolen, which it might be in the unlikely
event that you took your eyes off it for more than a second. No,
the PT (for ``personal transportation'') Cruiser is Pokemon hot.
Tickle-Me-Elmo hot. Cabbage Patch Kids hot. For those with a more
mature frame of reference, it is Mustang hot. It's been that long
(36 years, if you really must count) since any
</P>
<P>
   mass-produced American car rolled into the showrooms as a
gotta-have-one-right-now cultural phenomenon. (Kalajian, Palm Beach
Post).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RONCRUISER _ When Frances Buchanan faced throat surgery for
suspected cancer last winter, her husband, Glenn, made her a
promise. ``You're going to come through this surgery, and when you
do, we're buying you a new car, any car you want.'' Which struck
the mother of five as odd since she was fine with old cars and it
was her husband who was the car buff. ``Oh, really?'' she
</P>
<P>
   asked her husband, dryly. ``And just what car do I want, and
what color do I prefer?'' (Wiggins, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
