<P>
   CLASSIC CARS, ANCIENT CITY: The names come out a little
differently in Arabic. DeSoto becomes something like ``Tozata'' and
Chrysler sounds like ``Kleezler.'' But those old bombs you might
find in an auto collector's garage in America make for colorful and
practical transportation in Syria. The country's streets are flush
with fins and crawling with chrome. (Includes a 3-column color
photo of a classic car sitting in a garage, a 2-column detail shot
