SAN FRANCISCO _  WALK CAL  _ Gold Rush millionaire Sam Brannan laid
out Calistoga, his dream of a Saratoga Springs of the West, in the
1860s. More than 100 years later, it's location at the northern tip
of the Napa Valley makes it an Old West mecca for food-lovers. &HT;    With sidebar. 
 By Karola Saekel  
 c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
