week to repeal the federal estate tax, Democrats attack the
proposal as a gift to the rich. Republican leaders, who favor the
plan, say it would help farmers and small-business owners. We look
at who would benefit the most. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   SF-AIDS (Washington) _ San Francisco's share of federal money
for AIDS treatment and prevention per patient is nearly twice that
of other cities with high rates of the disease, the General
Accounting Office tells a congressional panel. Amid strong
resistance from lawmakers and officials in the San Francisco Bay
Area, key House negotiators have cut the city's share of AIDS funds
while increasing money for 50 other cities. By JUDY HOLLAND.
