   HIV-CHILDREN (Durban, South Africa) _ Of the estimated 10,000
American children born with HIV caused by mother-to-infant
infection, some 2,100 are now teen-agers, according to a new report
presented at the International AIDS Conference. These youngsters,
some of whom have been taking 15 to 17 pills a day for their entire
lives, are about to become sexually active. By LEIGH HOPPER.
</P>
