</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-MEDICAID (Austin, Texas) _ State Health and Human Services
Commissioner Don Gilbert says Texas is giving up efforts to recoup
$34 million in Medicaid claims paid to doctors over the past 22
years. The action is a response to doctors who threatened not to
participate in the program if the state continued the collection
efforts. By KATHY WALT.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-BIRTHS (Houston) _ Some hospitals have begun banning
couples from videotaping the birth of a child out of concern the
tapes could be used in lawsuits. The restriction stems from a $15
million settlement a hospital paid to a family that had claimed its
video showed evidence of malpractice. By LISA TEACHEY.
</P>
<P>
   SPACE-STATION (Houston) _ Hoping to cast aside a two-year legacy
of delay, Russia prepares to launch its large crew module to the
international space station. Secured atop a Proton rocket, the
43-foot-long spacecraft will house astronauts assigned to live and
work aboard the station. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
