<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A bonanza of bean variations
 &HT;    By Ann Heller
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio - Vary the basic green bean salad with these
additions. Toss just before serving with a simple vinaigrette.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Top with crumbled feta cheese and coarsely ground black
pepper.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Peel and cut crunchy jicama into batons _ shaped like the
beans. Figure on one pound of beans and half that much jicama.
Shower with snipped cilantro. Vary the dressing, using lime juice
and a light oil.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Arrange equal parts of cooked shell beans such as lima beans,
cranberry beans or green beans side by side on a platter. Snip
parsley and fresh chives over the top (in August, scatter the
blossoms of garlic chives over the beans).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Cook a pound each of green beans and wax beans. Cut a
quarter-pound of smoked mozzarella or smoked gouda into thin strips
and toss with the beans.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Toss the beans with several handfuls of halved, pitted
Kalamata olives.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Add a pint of halved cherry tomatoes to a pound of beans. Top
with slivered basil just before tossing with the dressing.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Toss with slivered salami, about a quarter-cup per pound of
beans, and the finely diced rounds of four green onions.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
