Elaine Wilson and Lois Curtis are expected to see their battle end
today. The historic case of ``EW'' and ``LC'' v. Olmstead, which
used the Americans with Disabilities Act to argue that
institutionalizing the mentally ill was a form of discrimination,
forced the 50 states to change the way they deal with the mentally
disabled. Today, they are expected to see what Georgia plans to do
and to reach a court-approved settlement to the local suit that
started the entire action. Today, both live in metro area group
homes, and we use the settlement to tell the story through their
eyes and experiences. (Osinski, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35.
