suspected cancer last winter, her husband, Glenn, made her a
promise. ``You're going to come through this surgery, and when you
do, we're buying you a new car, any car you want.'' Which struck
the mother of five as odd since she was fine with old cars and it
was her husband who was the car buff. ``Oh, really?'' she
</P>
