<P>
   BERNIE-DEPOT _ Bernie Marcus, a former stand-up comic and
hypnotist, has been the best icon Home Depot could hope for in the
company's 20-year history. Tough-talking and charming at once,
Marcus is Home Depot's do-it-yourself culture personified.
Colleagues describe him as a Pied Piper; employees routinely line
up for his autograph. But as the company prepares to double in size
over the next few yeasrs to nearly 2,000 stores, how is HD getting
the ``bleed orange'' message out to the masses? (Bonds, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   UPS _ The drivers of those chocolate brown trucks with gold trim
are known for moving packages at the ``speed of business'' from one
door to another. But the nation's largest parcel delivery service
is finding that moving packages is a lot easier than moving
Washington. ``Big Brown,'' as the company is commonly called, is
vying for a lucrative air route to China against another Alantny:
chocolate brown corrugated boxes filled with materials attacking
the U.S. Postal Service. Every member of the House got one of the
computer laptop-sized boxes. Tucked inside was a slick CD entitled,
``What The Postal Service Doesn't Want You to Know.'' There were
also negative news articles and a 16-page booklet that compared the
postal service to the CIA. (carr, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
