<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Wednesday, July 12 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   R-RATED-MOVIES (Los Angeles) _ The combination of big budget,
star and R rating may be the worst investment a Hollywood studio
can make, according to a new study. Research by a Texas A&AMP;M
economics professor has found the typical PG film generates three
times the revenue of the typical R-rated movie. By Erik Nelson.
(Will move in the ``a'' national, ``f'' financial and the ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DRUGS-MCCAFFREY (Los Angeles) _ U.S. drug czar Barry McCaffrey
formally announced he has a new initiative to encourage anti-drug
messages in Hollywood films. Unlike the controversial arrangements
with TV networks, however, there will be no direct financial
incentives for producers and directors. By Glenn Whipp and Bill
Hillburg. (Will move in the ``a'' national and the ``n'' California
news files.)
</P>
<P>
   AIDS-RISING (Los Angeles) _ Complacent because of new medicines
that prolong the life of AIDS patients, young gay men in Los
Angeles have been contracting HIV at a faster rate than the
national average, according to an L.A. County health study. By Rob
Monroe. (Will move in the ``a'' national and the ``n'' California
news files.)
</P>
