   BOSNIA-MEMORIAL (Srebrenica, Bosnia-Herzegovina) _ Thousands of
Muslim women and a few dozen men returned here for an emotionally
charged memorial service to the site where more than 7,000 men from
Srebrenica were taken away by attacking Serbian forces and killed.
They came in fleets of buses, under heavy police protection, many
of them returning for the first time to their hometown since those
fateful days in 1995, when they were separated from their menfolk
and herded on to buses to be deported. By Carlotta Gall. (The story
has moved in ``i'' news file.) 1,000 words.
</P>
