<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Clinton to attend Palm Beach fund-raiser
 &HT;    By Brian E. Crowley
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ President Clinton will be dropping by
the Colony Hotel and the home of Palm Beach County's Washington
lobbyist during a campaign trip here on July 31.
</P>
<P>
   Plans are still sketchy but Clinton is expected to arrive at the
Colony Hotel in Palm Beach in the early evening to attend a
$1,000-per-person money rasing event for U.S. Senate candidate Bill
Nelson.
</P>
<P>
   After that event, he will travel down the road to the Palm Beach
home of Eric and Colleen Hanson for another event raising money for
the Florida Democratic Party and the Democratic Senate Campaign
Committee.
</P>
<P>
   Eric Hanson is chairman of U.S. Strategies, a national lobbying
firm. He is also a major contributor to both Republican and
Democratic candidates. Two Democratic U.S. Senators, Tom Harkin of
Iowa and Tom Daschle of South Dakota, were groomsmen at his
wedding.
</P>
<P>
   Hanson was hired to be the county's Washington lobbyist last
year after some controversy over the failure of the commission to
seek bids for the job.
</P>
<P>
   Nelson, Florida's insurance commissioner, is being challenged by
Republican U.S. Rep. Bill McCollum of Altamonte Springs for the
Senate seat being vacated by Republican Connie Mack, who is
retiring. With just six seats needed to win control to the Senate,
both parties are focusing on this race.
</P>
<P>
   (salinity)briancrowley(at)pbpost.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
