   CHINA-PRIVATE-SECTOR (Jiaxing, China) _ China has been marching
on the road of economic reform for more than two decades now, but
its private sector remains a tiny slice of an economy still
dominated by government-owned organizations. Entrepreneurs are
systematically shunned by China's banks, discriminated against by
regulators and barred from entering many industries. Barriers to
capital formation keep most private businesses from providing more
than a handful of jobs, but there is growing pressure to change
that. By Craig S. Smith. (The story has moved in ``f'' news file.)
