 PERSONALS: Staying on Top of the Trends 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
A poll in the latest Ladies' Home Journal found that if voters were
ever to elect a female president,  &UR; Elizabeth Dole &LR;  and &UR; Hillary
Clinton &LR;  would be tied for 31 percent of the vote. Next most
popular candidate would be  &UR; Judge Judy &LR; , with 21 percent.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; AMERICA'S SWEETHEARTS SPEAK OUT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Darva Conger &LR; , the bride of a would-be millionaire who appears
in this month's Playboy, explained to the Chicago Sun-Times that
she posed because ``Playboy offers a safe haven, a comfortable,
credible way of making some money.''
