of European business travelers carry GSM phones. In the United
States, only a fraction of cellular customers have GSM service.
</P>
<P>
   The in-seat handsets also can be used to make calls, though this
is nothing new. Most airlines offer this service under brand names
like GTE Airfone and British Telecom Skyphone. But the new system
allows passengers for the first time to bill air-to-ground calls
through their cellular provider, Tharp said.
</P>
<P>
   The new system circumvents worldwide prohibitions against using
