that they could interfere with aircraft navigation systems.
</P>
<P>
   The prohibition, which is enforced on aircraft by the Federal
Aviation Administration, was instituted by the Federal
Communications Commission in landmark 1981 regulations that
reallocated certain radio frequencies to encourage growth and
competition in the fledgling cellular industry.
</P>
<P>
   Concerns about the potential for interference were important
