</P>
<P>
   The same frequencies can be used simultaneously in different
areas because a cell phone signal from the ground does not wander
much beyond its intended receiving station. But from an airplane
six miles high, cell phone signals reach the earth in a wide cone
that covers a big chunk of geography.
</P>
<P>
   ``The radio traffic-management system gets completely
undermined,'' Adler said. ``Potentially, with cellular calls from
airplanes, you'd have dozens and dozens of base stations receiving
