recent technological leap in a rapidly changing new era in which
airline passengers will ultimately have not only personal cell
phone service but also e-mail and broadband Internet access.
</P>
<P>
   But technology does not address the problem of bad cell phone
manners. Adler speculated that Americans in general are less
accustomed than Europeans to ambient public noise and therefore
more likely to speak unnecessarily loudly into a cell phone. He
says the cellular industry should consider mounting a publicity
