<HEADER>
A9647 &Cx1f; taf-z
u a BC-OBIT-RANDALL-NYT &LR;      07-11 0311
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OBIT-RANDALL-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WILLIAM RANDALL, 90, MISSOURI CONGRESSMAN WHO LED IMMIGRATION
PROBE 
</HEADLINE>
   By WOLFGANG SAXON   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Former Rep. William J. Randall, a conservative Democrat who
represented his native Independence, Mo., from 1959 to 1977, died
there on July 7. He was 90.
</P>
<P>
   Randall, a lawyer, was an unabashed champion of Independence,
the hometown of President Harry S. Truman.
</P>
<P>
   Randall, who represented Missouri's 4th Congressional District,
was sworn in on Capitol Hill in March 1959 after winning a special
election necessitated by the death of his predecessor, Rep. George
H. Christopher, another Democrat. After 16 years in the House,
Randall decided not to seek re-election in 1976.
</P>
<P>
   He was a member of the House Armed Services Committee and the
Government Operations Committee. As chairman of the latter
committee's Legal and Monetary Affairs Subcommittee, Randall came
to national prominence in the early 1970s when he conducted an
inquiry into illegal immigration from Mexico and charges of
corruption in the Southwest region of the Immigration and
Naturalization Service.
</P>
<P>
   In his last two years in Congress, Randall also headed a special
Select Committee on Aging, which conducted hearings on long-term
health care for the elderly.
</P>
<P>
   William Joseph Randall graduated from the University of Missouri
in 1931 and from the University of Kansas City's law school in
1936. He served with the Army in the Pacific in World War II.
</P>
<P>
   Randall then served on a Jackson County administrative court for
12 years until his election to Congress. When he left the House he
worked as a railroad lobbyist before returning to Independence,
where he had a private law practice.
</P>
<P>
   His wife of 47 years, Margaret Layden Randall, died in 1989.
Randall is survived by a daughter, Mary, two grandsons and a
great-granddaughter.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
