<SLUG> BC-FBN-IRVIN-NEXT-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IRVIN TRADES HIS GRABS FOR TV GAB
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEFF CAPLAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Talk about a natural transition.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Irvin, one of the NFL's all-time talkers, is taking his
talent to Fox Sports Net as an analyst on the cable network's ``NFL
This Morning'' pregame show, and on its nightly sports news show,
``National Sports Report''.
</P>
<P>
   Irvin, 34, revealed his future endeavors shortly after
announcing his retirement from the Dallas Cowboys on Tuesday at
Texas Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not doing this to kill time or fill a void,'' Irvin said.
``This is my career now. As hard as I worked in football, I will
work as hard on this. I am not going in this halfheartedly.''
</P>
<P>
   An electric, charismatic and passionate player for 12 seasons
with the Cowboys, Irvin has always been known for a sparkling smile
and his veracity to speak his mind. He received rave reviews after
making his television debut last season on ESPN's ``Game Day''
program.
</P>
<P>
   ``His competitive fire and outspoken candor,'' Arthur Smith, Fox
vice president of programming, production and news, said, ``will
give our shows a biting new perspective that will certainly
entertain football fans across the country,'' .
</P>
<P>
   On ``NFL This Morning'', Irvin joins a crew of host Chris Myers,
former Buffalo coach Marv Levy and former NFL stars Jackie Slater
and Chris Spielman. The show is seen live each week on Sunday
mornings at 10 a.m. Central time on Fox Sports Net.
</P>
<P>
   On ``National Sports Report'', which airs at 10 p.m. and
midnight Central nightly, Irvin joins Bill Maas, Cris Collinsworth,
Ron Pitts, Slater and Levy as NFL analysts.
</P>
<P>
   ``I am going to have a lot of fun with Marv,'' Irvin said,
referring to the 1992 and '93 seasons, when Irvin and the Cowboys
defeated Levy's Bills in back-to-back Super Bowls. ``Marv and I
have had a lot of encounters over the years. I'm sure he has a lot
to say to me.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
